# Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

## Context

Mistral Instruct v0.3 is a widely-used chat template format that wraps user turns with
`[INST]`/`[/INST]` markers, merges system messages into the first user turn, and appends
`</s>` (eos_token) after each assistant turn. The autoparser can handle it generically,
but a dedicated specialized handler provides more reliable tool-call structured generation,
explicit preservation of key tokens, and clearer debug logging.

The existing Ministral 3 handler already covers templates that carry `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` (e.g.
Ministral-3B, Mistral Small 3.2, Devstral). The new handler targets the complementary family
— templates that use `[INST]`/`[/INST]` but **do not** have `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` — which covers
`mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407` and the classic Mistral 7B/8x7B Instruct v0.3 family.

The constraint is: **only add new code to `common/chat.cpp`; do not touch any existing
handler, the header file, or any other file.**

---

## Critical Files

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `common/chat.cpp` | **Only file to edit.** All new code goes here. |
| `common/chat-peg-parser.h` | Read-only reference for `common_chat_peg_builder` API |
| `models/templates/mistralai-Mistral-Nemo-Instruct-2407.jinja` | Representative template for the target format |

---

## Existing Patterns to Reuse

All examples are in `common/chat.cpp`.

| Pattern / Helper | Where used | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `common_chat_template_direct_apply_impl(tmpl, inputs)` | every handler | renders the Jinja prompt |
| `build_chat_peg_parser(lambda)` | every handler | wraps PEG builder boilerplate |
| `p.standard_json_tools(section_start, section_end, tools, parallel, force, name_key, args_key, array_wrapped, …, call_id_key)` | declared in `chat-peg-parser.h` lines 108-119 | **perfect fit** for `[TOOL_CALLS][{name, arguments, id}]` format; pass `array_wrapped=true`, `call_id_key="id"` |
| `p.trigger_rule("tool-call", …)` | Ministral 3, GigaChat v3, others | activates grammar on tool call start |
